<section id="architecture" class="section--lg arch">
  <div class="container reveal">
    <header class="arch__header">
      <p class="eyebrow">Architecture</p>
      <h2 class="display">Serverless on your LAN. Zero-knowledge beyond it.</h2>
      <p class="lede">Every channel is peer-to-peer, and each one is chosen for its job &mdash; ordered control state, latency-sensitive media, and an end-to-end-encrypted lane for messages.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="pane pane--raised arch__table">
      <ol class="arch__lanes" aria-label="Peer-to-peer transport lanes">
        <li class="arch__row">
          <div class="arch__lane">
            <span class="arch__lane-no" aria-hidden="true">Lane 1</span>
            <h3 class="title">Control</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="arch__proto"><span class="arch__term">MultipeerConnectivity</span></p>
          <p class="arch__payload">Workspace state, tab selection, trackpad deltas, voice text, <kbd class="keycap">Enter</kbd>. An <code class="arch__code">MCSession</code> with encryption required, service type <code class="arch__code">blau-sync</code>.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="arch__row">
          <div class="arch__lane">
            <span class="arch__lane-no" aria-hidden="true">Lane 2</span>
            <h3 class="title">Media</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="arch__proto">Network.framework <span class="arch__term">TCP</span></p>
          <p class="arch__payload">HEVC frames, keyframe requests, link stats. <code class="arch__code">_blau-frames._tcp</code> on Bonjour, including peer-to-peer Wi-Fi (AWDL), so no shared router is required.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="arch__row">
          <div class="arch__lane">
            <span class="arch__lane-no" aria-hidden="true">Lane 3</span>
            <h3 class="title">Annotation</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="arch__proto">Network.framework <span class="arch__term">TCP</span></p>
          <p class="arch__payload">Pencil strokes, undo, clear &mdash; both directions. Its own channel: <code class="arch__code">_blau-annotate._tcp</code>.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="arch__row">
          <div class="arch__lane">
            <span class="arch__lane-no" aria-hidden="true">Lane 4</span>
            <h3 class="title">Watch</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="arch__proto"><span class="arch__term">WatchConnectivity</span></p>
          <p class="arch__payload">Double-pinch &rarr; <kbd class="keycap">Enter</kbd>, with guaranteed background transfer as the fallback when the phone is unreachable.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="arch__row">
          <div class="arch__lane">
            <span class="arch__lane-no" aria-hidden="true">Lane 5</span>
            <h3 class="title">Secure Messaging</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="arch__proto"><span class="arch__term">Noise IK</span> over UDP</p>
          <p class="arch__payload">End-to-end encrypted messaging between Pilot and Copilot across networks: <code class="arch__code">X25519 + ChaChaPoly</code> via <code class="arch__code">CryptoKit</code>, NAT hole punching, ACK'd delivery with replay protection. Keys exchange automatically over the Multipeer channel.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <p class="arch__footnote mono small"><span class="arch__footnote-label">FOOTNOTE&nbsp;&mdash;</span> One server exists. A Cloudflare rendezvous worker brokers <span class="arch__footnote-key">&#123;public key, IP, port&#125;</span> so two devices on different networks can hole-punch &mdash; it never sees plaintext or session keys, and it's contacted only for cross-network messaging. Everything else never leaves your local network.</p>
  </div>
</section>
